üìå The first mistake to avoid when learning to become a data scientist is focusing too much on coding at the expense of understanding statistics and machine learning, which are the core knowledge areas.

üßê It's not necessary to become a data analyst before pursuing a career as a data scientist, as the skill sets and focus areas differ between the two roles.

n. üöÄ Following a structured plan, treating job search as a project, and incorporating generative AI, communication skills, and practical application beyond regression are crucial aspects to consider in the journey to becoming a successful data scientist.
